# ─── Per-instance configuration ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env` (next to docker-compose.yml) and fill in the
# values for *your* deployment. The repo's .gitignore excludes `.env`, so
# your real values stay local.
#
# Vite reads these at build-time (`envDir: ".."` in vite.config.ts) and
# inlines them into the static bundle. The Docker build picks them up via
# build args declared in docker-compose.yml + Dockerfile.
#
# After changing any value, rebuild: `docker compose up -d --build`.

# ─── Imprint (German § 5 DDG / § 18 MStV requires this on a publicly
#     reachable URL). When ANY of NAME / ADDRESS_LINE_1 / ADDRESS_LINE_2 /
#     EMAIL is missing, /impressum renders an "Imprint not configured"
#     placeholder so you notice before the public does. ─────────────────
VITE_IMPRESSUM_NAME="Your Name"
VITE_IMPRESSUM_ADDRESS_LINE_1="Street 1"
VITE_IMPRESSUM_ADDRESS_LINE_2="12345 City"
VITE_IMPRESSUM_COUNTRY="Deutschland"
VITE_IMPRESSUM_EMAIL="you@example.org"

# ─── Data-protection supervisory authority (DSGVO Art. 77).
#     Optional. If omitted, /datenschutz falls back to a generic
#     "supervisory authority depends on controller's seat" notice. ─────
#     The default below is for an operator based in Bavaria.
VITE_DSGVO_AUTHORITY_NAME="Bayerisches Landesamt für Datenschutzaufsicht (BayLDA)"
VITE_DSGVO_AUTHORITY_ADDRESS="Promenade 18, 91522 Ansbach"
